      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:1:2:20:1",
      "text": [
        " إِنَّ اللَّهَ تَبَارَكَ وَ تَعَالَى أَنْزَلَ فِي الْقُرْآنِ تِبْيَانَ كُلِّ شَيْ‏ءٍ حَتَّى وَ اللَّهِ مَا تَرَكَ اللَّهُ شَيْئاً يَحْتَاجُ إِلَيْهِ الْعِبَادُ حَتَّى لَا يَسْتَطِيعَ عَبْدٌ يَقُولُ لَوْ كَانَ هَذَا أُنْزِلَ فِي الْقُرْآنِ إِلَّا وَ قَدْ أَنْزَلَهُ اللَّهُ فِيهِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Isa, from Ali Bin Hadeed, from Murazim, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Allah<sup>azwj</sup> Blessed and High Revealed in the Quran an explanation of everything to the extent that, by Allah<sup>azwj</sup>, Allah<sup>azwj</sup> did not neglect anything which the servants would be needy to, until there is no capacity for a servant to be saying, ‘If only this (matter) had been Revealed in the Quran’, except that Allah<sup>azwj</sup> has Revealed in it’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          " That there is nothing about lawful and unlawful matters that may have been left without a rule in the book and the Sunnah."
        ]
      }
    },
